Usage: {{.ProgName}} <markdown-filename> [-nocss] [-title <title>] [-header "<header-content>"]...

Converts a Markdown file into an HTML file.

Options:
  -nocss                     Do not include default CSS in the output HTML.
  -title <title>             Set the title of the HTML document.
  -header "<header-content>" Append a custom string to the output before the body
                             (e.g., custom <meta> tags, <script>, or <style>).
                             Can be specified multiple times.

Examples:
  # Basic conversion with CSS
  {{.ProgName}} README.md

  # Conversion without CSS
  {{.ProgName}} README.md -nocss

  # Set a custom title and add meta charset
  {{.ProgName}} README.md -title "My Page" -header "<meta charset='utf-8'>"
